<br>
Now the problem is I know nothing about mercs. /laughs <br>
<br>
I was looking back for posts with advise on speccing and strategies for Mercs I'm having difficulty finding this. I have a new Merc that is Briton I'm going to spec slash. I haven't yet put points into anything else but do expect to go DW. My main aim of course is RvR. <br>
<br>
Any advise on specs and strategies (I expect it's a bit different from a pole Armswoman) would be very much appreciated. In other words I need a Merc education. Links to good threads or sites would also help. <br>
<br>
Thanks a bunch. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fester@lighttanksofdaoc>Fester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#000000>(6/11/03 7:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> There is a good thread on the VN boards in the Albion Fighter.. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=51521519&replies=33">vnboards.ign.com/message....replies=33</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tatsumaruiii>TatsumaruIII</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#000000>(6/11/03 7:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> Sad to say, raising my armsman is almost -just- like my merc. somewhat different problems, but same end result - eating dirt. Not able to dish out the damage required, nor able to take the punishment long enough to deal with the damage I do now. These situations seem to be common amongs most of the tanks, but albion tends to feel it most, since we're the supposed defensive realm yet our defense is comparable to the other realms.<br>
<br>
However, on a happier note, I like my merc a lot, and hence the similaritys between the arms and merc (two hander arms, btw) causes me to like my arms alot. The few good events I encounter outweight the more bad events. It's all about attitude, anyways. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have a feeling what you're trying to escape from, isn't something that can be outruned. Least, not in albion. Our main tanks are being out-damaged and out-tanked by the other realms counterparts, like our light tanks are with their counter-parts.<br>
<br>
But, you never know. We still get by in our own ways. In a sense, that almost makes me feel fixed. Aslong as you don't care about being uber, this class should suit you fine. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
Voas - 24 Scout</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(6/11/03 9:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> No, I'm not looking to be uber and I'm retiring my Armswoman because of problems I consider particular to the offensive armsman rather than to melee or Albion in general. I have to say until very recently my experiences with my Armswoman in RvR were much more positive than negative. I've just run out of patience with the problems of the class and now it's getting harder to get past the tanks with block to get to the casters that are supposed to be the Armsman's targets. It's time for a change. for me. <br>
<br>
Anyway any hints as to spec, etc would be much appreciated and thanks for the link.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fingoniel>Fingoniel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://forums.barrysworld.com/avatar.php?userid=16042&dateline=1026917502" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 334<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 3:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> tatsumaru's just being bitter :P <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  mercs are doing fine - just they're a pure tank, so like an armsman you need a good group to do anything well. <br>
<br>
We rely on other people's buffs, other people healing etc. but if we have all that we're the best out there.<br>
<br>
As for spec...<br>
<br>
If you're set on slash/dw the most common specs are 50 slash 50 dw 28 parry<br>
or if you want you can go 50 dual 44 slash 37 parry (my fave spec <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <br>
or if yer completely insane and would like to be able to pull out a shield, look like a cleric and play defensive...<br>
<br>
50 dual 42 slash 32 parry 23 shield <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
for levelling up - put lots into slash and dual wield, maybe save some for parry (although you don't get it till level 17 - maybe just put all of level 17s points into parry)<br>
<br>
can't really go wrong <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Fingoniel MacAlpine<br>
Captain of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.humbertonguard.tk">Humberton Guard</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Ererim the Magma Wizard<br>
Even more alts....</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwerraldarkmorn>Gwerral Darkmorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 5:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> now it's getting harder to get past the tanks with block to get to the casters that are supposed to be the Armsman's targets.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Ummm...  If you're swinging a pole, casters probably shouldn't be your first target - you would have a difficult time getting through pulsing bladeturn unless you're paired with someone using faster weapons who can keep the bubble down.  If I'm not assisting, casters and healers are my targets (along with any assassins in the group) and the heavy tanks and hybrids take care of the opposing realm's tanks. <p>Gwerral Darkmorn<br>
Master Crushing Mercenary<br>
Legendary Smith<br>
&lt;The Illuminati&gt;<br>
Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 7:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> Yes, casters and healers were my main targets. Yes, they generally are the main targets for armsmen. Tanks are &quot;mop up work&quot; though this is less so than it used to be. And yes  a pole armsman pretty much has to have a bubble popper along for the ride. I specced thrust with her specifically to target healers as a matter of fact. I actually don't need advice on Arms tactics having played one pretty steadily for the last year. <br>
<br>
Now a Merc is a different situation. I've played along side them but don't know that much about how they'r specced, and have a lot to learn. Thanks for the help.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 7:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> Why on earth would anyone spec shield over 7 on a Merc?! You can't even use a large shield. I can see a merc carrying a shield to attract attackers as they're easily mistkaen for clerics but why would you spec? <br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwerraldarkmorn>Gwerral Darkmorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 8:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> With 7 shield, you get engage and guard I.  It's useful while running down archers as they're attacking you (engage them and they rarely hit you) or for placing a &quot;ghetto guard&quot; on a caster when you're short on shield tanks.  Yes, my puny medium shield with 7 spec has saved a wizard's life even before the blocking changes.<br>
<br>
As for disguise...  when I'm really bored, you can find me running through the Pennines along the stone paths with my torch on and my shield out.  (I'm a crush merc)  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Gwerral Darkmorn<br>
Master Crushing Mercenary<br>
Legendary Smith<br>
&lt;The Illuminati&gt;<br>
Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lemonade@lighttanksofdaoc>Lemonade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/relic/Xid.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 10:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> For your information I am a shield Mercenary. Yes you heard me I am a shield Mercenary and it works a heck of alot better for me than two weapons especially for RVR in that sometimes you don't even swing a left and the DW spec line sucks because of lack of an anytime style. I gave up chance to swing a second weapon and some styles whoopdee.<br>
<br>
Slam is a very versatile move it can be used in defense and offense and especially useful against enemy casters which will mow you down when given the chance and everyone hates MOC + PBAE =0). While Slam not being the only thing shield is good for it gives you a chance to block which is great for parry's weakness being 2-hand.  <br>
<br>
So you say why not be an Armsman well here is your answer:<br>
A.) Evade is very useful ESPECIALLY against other shield tanks they can't land shield styles too often and you can even evade from behind. <br>
B.) Different armor resist table being crush resistant is better than having it as weakness IMO since theirs not too many enemy thrust users. <br>
C.) Flurry,Charge, and Dirty Tricks are very useful and add alot of utility.<br>
<br>
&quot;THE LIGHT TANK EXPLAINED&quot; - 1.62B Patch Notes<br>
<br>
&quot;There's been a lot of discussion, controversy, and misunderstanding about light tanks in Dark Age of Camelot. The purpose the light tank was designed for was to be a damage dealer, but not have much defense.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ok now here is a question were supposed to be designed for a damage dealer and not have much defense then why the heck do Mercenary and Blademaster get Shield spec?<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Lemonade 50 Shield Mercenary Merlin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 2:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> Yes, those are advantages you listed but it's hard to see that they outweigh having to use a medium shield and only being able to block 2 opponents. But if it works well for you, that's great. No insult intended, Lemonade.<br>
<br>
Gwerral Darkmorn, what you mentioned was why I intend to spec shield to 7. It's very useful. I doubt I'll keep my spec crush though. Most likely I'll respec at 40. Still being mistaken for a cleric might be fun. /grins<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A> at: 6/12/03 3:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 3:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> Honestly if one was to start a new character and wanted to have reasonably high shield spec, they are better off making an armsman.<br>
<br>
That doesn't mean shield spec isn't viable for mercenaries, mainly because dual wield isn't that great. And speccing in shield more than makes up for flurry or the low offhand damage when it doesn't miss.<br>
<br>
And it's better than leveling a new character for high level mercs looking for a change.<br>
<br>
As for why mercs can spec in shield. Just another option. Just like armsman can spec in xbow even though it's not really rewarding because their other spec lines are much better for the role they typically play. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fester@lighttanksofdaoc>Fester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 4:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> I dueled a fellow Merc last night on my server who is Shield.  We dueled multiple times (not using dirt) and I always ended up having 80% life left when he went down. He had better passives than me (he has MoPain 2, i have Mopain1, he has MoParry 2, I have MoParry1). <br>
<br>
He slamed me each time and did Amy+Diamond combos (most of which I parried (i am 50DW/44slash/37parry).<br>
<br>
I had an easier time with him than I do vs armsmen. Armsmen can get me down to 20% health/win. <br>
<br>
In the old days, it was cool to be a shield merc because people thought you were a cleric... now with Reavers out it doesn't really make a difference. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 6:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> With a Briton it looks to me like thrust is out so I'm pretty narrowed down to either keeping crush or re-speccing to slash. The styles (and growth rate) on slash look better so I think I'll end up re-speccing. <br>
<br>
That leaves the issue of spec. A lot of people have said the best way to go is 50 DW/ 50 slash/ 28 parry. (The low parry looks a bit scary but you can make it up with + items and MoParry.) Other Mercs have told me they're very happy with either 50DW/44slash/37parry or 50 slash/44 DW/37 parry.  <br>
<br>
Any comments or suggestions to put me in the right direction? My new Merc is still in her 20s. I'm getting some powerleveling and playing her for levels. Don't want to end up a PL baby at 50 with no clue how to play. <br>
<br>
Thanks for all the info and suggestions.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blame@lighttanksofdaoc>Blame</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://homepages.internet.lu/lordoftherings/images/boromir.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Determined Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 431<br> <font color=#000000>(6/14/03 11:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> info on 50-slash</span><hr size=1> OK, I guess the question you're asking is, do you want Diamond Slash, the lvl 50 Slash style.<br>
<br>
OK, it's got a 93% growth rate, and follows on from Ammy. The chain has a great to-hit chance, no stupid bleeds, it's just pure damage from the sharp side.<br>
<br>
It's problem is that it drinks endurance by the bucketfull. However, if you've got a Paladin's endurance chant, you can do it non-stop. The average damag eof the chain ends out at about 88/89%, which is the same as BackSlash (lvl 39 Slash style) spammed repeatedly (only you don't have to be behind the target to do this chain).<br>
<br>
Dslash may or may not be superior to a spamming of DShadows, lvl 50 DW style with a 79% growth rate. DShadows has a medium defensive penalty and seems to miss more often. But each hit of DShadows starts a bleed at 20-ish damage. Not sure if this 20 damage makes up for the average loss of 20% growth rate in comparison to the chain. I guess it depends what weapons you're using...<br>
<br>
Well, the damage is noticeably bigger than anything you've hit for yet, with the possible exception of Shadows Rain. When you're smacking lower-con mobs (particularly GREENS! muhaha... ) you will notice a HUGE alternation in your swings from OK damage to awesome damage.<br>
<br>
My verdict on 28 parry? Well, unbuffed, don't count on parrying much, even with capped Dex, if it's another player. Especially not a 2H one.<br>
<br>
If it's yellow or orange mobs, you can probably get a couple of opportunities to pull off the reactionaries, which seem to be getting an overhaul while Slash styles are staying the same in the hands of a mercenary.<br>
<br>
If your parry is 28 you will DEFINITELY want to add +11 from items at level 50. I myself am regretfully losing Diamond Slash when I get my respec, so that I can benefit mroe from the parry change (and the upgraded DW styles which all rely on parrying it seeems).<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosimond@lighttanksofdaoc>Rosimond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#000000>(6/15/03 11:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=256.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need advise on a new merc </span><hr size=1> I do see that a there are a number of DW styles that work off parry so a good parry would be an advantage for using these. Would 50 DW/39 slash/39 parry be a reasonable template in that case? I realize you wouldn't have the highest slash styles but you'd still have ammy as a backup for the DW styles. With + items and MoParry I should think you'd get a fair number of parries. <br>
<br>
Just as a thought, this seems to me to contradict the usual line of thought that Mercs are intended to attack support and not tanks. You'll rarely parry against them. Any thoughts on this? I play on Percy. What classes should I be speccing to target?<br>
